{
  "genre": "ambient",
  "mode": "energize",
  "mixStrategy": "This ambient/atmospheric energize arrangement uses four pad layers that build from a gentle wash into a shimmering, driving wall of sound, then recede gracefully. FREQUENCY SEPARATION: The Warm Pad bass (C2-C3, 20-300Hz) provides the sub-foundation with long droning roots that anchor every harmonic shift. The Choir Pad chords (C3-C5, 300Hz-2kHz) fill the harmonic body with open sus2/maj7 voicings \u2014 root-5th-9th spacing to keep them airy yet present. The New Age Pad melody (C4-C6, 1-8kHz) floats above with shimmering melodic phrases built from chord tones on strong beats and Lydian passing tones (#4, maj7) on weak beats. The Sweep Pad texture (C5-G5, 3kHz+) adds crystalline shimmer and evolving high-frequency air. HARMONIC UNITY: All tracks follow Csus2 \u2192 Fmaj7 \u2192 Cmaj7 \u2192 Am simultaneously. In C Lydian: C-D-E-F#-G-A-B. The sus2 chords use C-D-G, Fmaj7 uses F-A-C-E, Cmaj7 uses C-E-G-B, Am uses A-C-E. Chord changes happen every ~11.25 seconds (segments of the 45s piece). ENERGY ARC: Segments 0-7.5s (0.4 energy) \u2014 sparse, few voices, low velocity. 7.5-15s (0.6) \u2014 more notes enter, chords thicken. 15-22.5s (0.8) \u2014 melody becomes more active, bass pulses subtly. 22.5-30s (0.9) \u2014 full density, highest velocities, all layers active. 30-37.5s (1.0) \u2014 peak energy, fastest melodic movement, richest chords. 37.5-45s (0.7) \u2014 graceful descent, thinning out, velocities drop. RHYTHMIC INTERLOCK: Despite ambient genre, the ENERGIZE mode means notes have shorter sustains (1-4s for melody, 2-6s for chords) creating a pulsing, breathing quality rather than static drones. Bass provides slow rhythmic anchoring while melody creates forward motion with overlapping phrases. All tracks breathe together \u2014 when melody rests, texture fills; when chords shift, bass moves first as a signal.",
